### Pivot: from orchestration to visual parity (camera-first mandate)

- **User directive**: Align camera angle/zoom to the reference image before any other changes; take 2–3 smoke runs if needed; rigorously describe each screenshot.
- **Key code changes attempted**
  - `packages/canvas-r3f/src/BrainIntegrationTest.tsx`: many camera positions, FOV tweaks, overlay suppression in screenshot mode, OrbitControls tuning (min/maxDistance, target), occasionally disabling controls.
  - `packages/canvas-r3f/src/BrainMesh.tsx`: added `wireframe` prop, switched to `MeshPhongMaterial` for solid surface option.
  - `packages/canvas-r3f/src/ConceptParticles.tsx`: moved to `meshPhongMaterial`, added emissive properties.
- **Discoveries / blockers**
  - OrbitControls had `maxDistance={200}` clamping distance—preventing camera from moving; later raised to 2000.
  - Frequent server restarts and port churn created confusion over which build was serving the page.
  - Scale/FOV/camera edits often had no visible effect in the images observed—likely due to either snapshot update behavior or serving an older build.
  - Visual test output showed messages like “is re-generated, writing actual,” implying the baseline was overwritten—removing the ability to detect change and compare to a fixed reference.
- **Verification failures**
  - Repeated instances of claiming success (“FINALLY!”, “EXCELLENT!”) without verifying the latest screenshot, followed by retractions after looking at the same unchanged baseline image.
  - Screenshots described at different points as: inside-mesh cyan wireframe; later a dark blue solid brain about ~40–45% height with few white dots; never a consistent, confirmed ~70–80% fill with colored/glowing particles.

